Arrow keys = Move to the adjacent item in a list, tab group, or menu, or move sliders and adjusters (Up Arrow to increase values, Down Arrow to decrease values).
Fn← = Home: Scroll to the beginning of a document.
Fn↑ = Page Up: Scroll up one page.
Fn→ Arrow = End: Scroll to the end of a document.
Fn↓ = Page Down: Scroll down one page.
Fn⌃F2 = Move focus to the menu bar. (Alternative key combination)
Fn⌃F3 = Move focus to the Dock. (Alternative key combination)
Fn⌃F4 = Move focus to the active window or next window. (Alternative key combination)
Fn⌃F5 = Move focus to the window toolbar. (Alternative key combination)
Fn⌃F6 = Move focus to the floating window. (Alternative key combination)
Fn⌃F7 = Change the way Tab moves focus—between navigation of all controls on the screen, or only text boxes and lists. (Alternative key combination)
Fn⌃F8 = Move focus to the status menu in the menu bar. (Alternative key combination)
Fn⌫ = Forward delete on keyboards that don not have a Forward Delete key. Or use Control-D.
Power button = Press to turn on your Mac or wake it from sleep. Press and hold for 1.5 seconds to put your Mac to sleep. Continue holding to force your Mac to turn off.
Space bar = Use Quick Look to preview the selected item.
Tab = Move to next control.
← = Close the selected folder. This works only when in list view.
→ Arrow = Open the selected folder. This works only when in list view.
⇧Tab = Move to previous control.
⇧← = Extend text selection one character to the left.
⇧↑ = Extend text selection to the nearest character at the same horizontal location on the line above.
⇧→ Arrow = Extend text selection one character to the right.
⇧↓ = Extend text selection to the nearest character at the same horizontal location on the line below.
⇧⌘+ = Increase the size of the selected item. Command–Equal sign (=) performs the same function.
⇧⌘- = Decrease the size of the selected item.
⇧⌘5 = In macOS Mojave or later, take a screenshot or make a screen recording. Or use Shift-Command-3 or Shift-Command-4 for screenshots.
⇧⌘: = Display the Spelling and Grammar window.
⇧⌘? = Open the Help menu.
⇧⌘C = Open the Computer window.
⇧⌘D = Open the desktop folder.
⇧⌘F = Open the Recents window, showing all of the files you viewed or changed recently.
⇧⌘G = Open a Go to Folder window.
⇧⌘Grave accent (`) = Activate the previous open window in the front app.
⇧⌘H = Open the Home folder of the current macOS user account.
⇧⌘I = Open iCloud Drive.
⇧⌘K = Open the Network window.
⇧⌘N = Create a new folder in the Finder.
⇧⌘N = Create a new folder.
⇧⌘O = Open the Documents folder.
⇧⌘P = Page setup: Display a window for selecting document settings.
⇧⌘P = Show or hide the Preview pane in Finder windows.
⇧⌘Q = Log out of your macOS user account. You will be asked to confirm. To log out immediately without confirming, press Option-Shift-Command-Q.
⇧⌘R = Open the AirDrop window.
⇧⌘S = Display the Save As dialog, or duplicate the current document.
⇧⌘T = Show or hide the tab bar in Finder windows.
⇧⌘U = Open the Utilities folder.
⇧⌘| = Center align.
⇧⌘← = Select the text between the insertion point and the beginning of the current line.
⇧⌘↑ = Select the text between the insertion point and the beginning of the document.
⇧⌘→ Arrow = Select the text between the insertion point and the end of the current line.
⇧⌘↓ = Select the text between the insertion point and the end of the document.
⇧⌘⌫ = Empty the Trash.
⌃A = Move to the beginning of the line or paragraph.
⌃Arrow keys = Move to a control adjacent to the text field.
⌃B = Move one character backward.
⌃B→ness ↓ = Change the brightness of your external display, if supported by your display.
⌃D = Delete the character to the right of the insertion point. Or use Fn-Delete.
⌃E = Move to the end of a line or paragraph.
⌃F = Move one character forward.
⌃F2 = Move focus to the menu bar. You can then use the arrow keys to navigate the menu, press Return to open a selected menu or choose a selected menu item, or type the menu item is name to jump to that item in the selected menu.
⌃F3 = Move focus to the Dock.
⌃F4 = Move focus to the active window or next window.
⌃F5 = Move focus to the window toolbar.
⌃F6 = Move focus to the floating window.
⌃F7 = Change the way Tab moves focus—between navigation of all controls on the screen, or only text boxes and lists.
⌃F8 = Move focus to the status menu in the menu bar.
⌃H = Delete the character to the left of the insertion point. Or use Delete.
⌃K = Delete the text between the insertion point and the end of the line or paragraph.
⌃L = Center the cursor or selection in the visible area.
⌃N = Move down one line.
⌃O = Insert a new line after the insertion point.
⌃P = Move up one line.
⌃Power button = Display a dialog asking whether you want to restart, sleep, or shut down.
⌃T = Swap the character behind the insertion point with the character in front of the insertion point.
⌃Tab = Move to the next control when a text field is selected.
⌃↓ = Show all windows of the front app.
⌃⇧F6 = Move focus to the previous panel.
⌃⇧Power button = Put your displays to sleep.
⌃⇧Tab = Move to the previous grouping of controls.
⌃⇧⌘T = Add selected Finder item to the Dock (OS X Mavericks or later)
⌃⌘A = Make an alias of the selected item.
⌃⌘D = Show or hide the definition of the selected word.
⌃⌘F = Use the app in full screen, if supported by the app.
⌃⌘Media Eject = Quit all apps, then restart your Mac. If any open documents have unsaved changes, you will be asked whether you want to save them.
⌃⌘Power button = Force your Mac to restart, without prompting to save any open and unsaved documents.
⌃⌘Q = Immediately lock your screen.
⌃⌘Space bar = Show the Character Viewer, from which you can choose emoji and other symbols.
⌃⌘T = Add the selected item to the sidebar (OS X Mavericks or later).
⌃⌥⌘, = Reduce contrast.
⌃⌥⌘. = Increase contrast.
⌃⌥⌘8 = Invert colors.
⌃⌥⌘Power button = Quit all apps, then shut down your Mac. If any open documents have unsaved changes, you will be asked whether you want to save them.
⌘ = Click a window title: See the folders that contain the current folder.
⌘ = Key while dragging to another volume: Move the dragged item to the other volume, instead of copying it.
⌘1 = View the items in the Finder window as icons.
⌘2 = View the items in a Finder window as a list.
⌘3 = View the items in a Finder window in columns.
⌘4 = View the items in a Finder window in a gallery.
⌘; = Find misspelled words in the document.
⌘A = Select All items.
⌘B = Boldface the selected text, or turn boldfacing on or off.
⌘B→ness ↓ = Turn video mirroring on or off when your Mac is connected to more than one display.
⌘C = Copy the selected item to the Clipboard. This also works for files in the Finder.
⌘Comma (,) = Open preferences for the front app.
⌘D = Duplicate the selected files.
⌘D = Select the Desktop folder from within an Open dialog or Save dialog.
⌘E = Eject the selected disk or volume.
⌘F = Find items in a document or open a Find window.
⌘F = Start a Spotlight search in the Finder window.
⌘G = Find Again: Find the next occurrence of the item previously found. To find the previous occurrence, press Shift-Command-G.
⌘Grave accent (`) = Activate the next open window in the front app.
⌘Grave accent (`) = Switch between the windows of the app you are using.
⌘H = Hide the windows of the front app. To view the front app but hide all other apps, press Option-Command-H.
⌘I = Italicize the selected text, or turn italics on or off.
⌘I = Show the Get Info window for a selected file.
⌘J = Show View Options.
⌘K = Add a web link.
⌘K = Open the Connect to Server window.
⌘M = Minimize the front window to the Dock. To minimize all windows of the front app, press Option-Command-M.
⌘Mission ⌃ = Show the desktop.
⌘N = Open a new Finder window.
⌘O = Open the selected item, or open a dialog to select a file to open.
⌘P = Print the current document.
⌘R = (1) When an alias is selected in the Finder: show the original file for the selected alias. (2) In some apps, such as Calendar or Safari, refresh or reload the page. (3) In Software Update, check for software updates again.
⌘S = Save the current document.
⌘Slash (/) = Hide or show the status bar in Finder windows.
⌘Space bar = Show or hide the Spotlight search field. To perform a Spotlight search from a Finder window, press Command–Option–Space bar.
⌘T = Open a new tab.
⌘T = Show or hide the Fonts window.
⌘T = Show or hide the tab bar when a single tab is open in the current Finder window.
⌘Tab = Switch to the next most recently used app among your open apps.
⌘U = Underline the selected text, or turn underlining on or off.
⌘V = Paste the contents of the Clipboard into the current document or app. This also works for files in the Finder.
⌘W = Close the front window. To close all windows of the app, press Option-Command-W.
⌘while double-clicking = Open a folder in a separate tab or window.
⌘X = Cut the selected item and copy it to the Clipboard.
⌘Y = Use Quick Look to preview the selected files.
⌘Z = Undo the previous command. You can then press Shift-Command-Z to Redo, reversing the undo command. In some apps, you can undo and redo multiple commands.
⌘← = Move the insertion point to the beginning of the current line.
⌘← Bracket ([) = Go to the previous folder.
⌘← Curly Bracket{ = Left align.
⌘↑ = Move the insertion point to the beginning of the document.
⌘↑ = Open the folder that contains the current folder.
⌘→ Arrow = Move the insertion point to the end of the current line.
⌘→ Bracket (]) = Go to the next folder.
⌘→ Curly Bracket} = Right align.
⌘↓ = Move the insertion point to the end of the document.
⌘↓ = Open the selected item.
⌘⌃↑ = Open the folder that contains the current folder in a new window.
⌘⌫ = Move the selected item to the Trash.
⌥ = Click a disclosure triangle: Open all folders within the selected folder. This works only when in list view.
⌥ = Key while dragging: Copy the dragged item. The pointer changes while you drag the item.
⌥B→ness ↑ = Open Displays preferences. This works with either Brightness key.
⌥Key while double-clicking = Open the item in a separate window, then close the original window.
⌥Keyboard B→ness ↑ = Open Keyboard preferences. This works with either Keyboard Brightness key.
⌥Mission ⌃ = Open Mission Control preferences.
⌥Volume ↑ = Open Sound preferences. This works with any of the volume keys.
⌥← = Move the insertion point to the beginning of the previous word.
⌥→ Arrow = Move the insertion point to the end of the next word.
⌥⇧B→ness ↑ = Adjust the display brightness in smaller steps.
⌥⇧B→ness ↓ = Adjust the display brightness in smaller steps. Add the Control key to this shortcut to make the adjustment on your external display, if supported by your display.
⌥⇧Keyboard B→ness ↑ = Adjust the keyboard brightness in smaller steps.
⌥⇧Volume ↑ = Adjust the sound volume in smaller steps.
⌥⇧← = Extend text selection to the beginning of the current word, then to the beginning of the following word if pressed again.
⌥⇧↑ = Extend text selection to the beginning of the current paragraph, then to the beginning of the following paragraph if pressed again.
⌥⇧→ Arrow = Extend text selection to the end of the current word, then to the end of the following word if pressed again.
⌥⇧↓ = Extend text selection to the end of the current paragraph, then to the end of the following paragraph if pressed again.
⌥⇧⌘V = Paste and Match Style: Apply the style of the surrounding content to the item pasted within that content.
⌥⇧⌘⌫ = Empty the Trash without confirmation dialog.
⌥⌘ = While dragging: Make an alias of the dragged item. The pointer changes while you drag the item.
⌥⌘C = Copy Style: Copy the formatting settings of the selected item to the Clipboard.
⌥⌘D = Show or hide the Dock.
⌥⌘F = Go to the search field.
⌥⌘Grave accent (`) = Move the focus to the window drawer.
⌥⌘I = Show or hide the inspector window.
⌥⌘L = Open the Downloads folder.
⌥⌘N = Create a new Smart Folder.
⌥⌘P = Hide or show the path bar in Finder windows.
⌥⌘Power button = Put your Mac to sleep.
⌥⌘S = Hide or show the Sidebar in Finder windows.
⌥⌘T = Show or hide a toolbar in the app.
⌥⌘T = Show or hide the toolbar when a single tab is open in the current Finder window.
⌥⌘V = Move the files in the Clipboard from their original location to the current location.
⌥⌘V = Paste Style: Apply the copied style to the selected item.
⌥⌘Y = View a Quick Look slideshow of the selected files.
⌥⌘⎋ = Force quit an app.
⌥⌫ = Delete the word to the left of the insertion point.